# Naming Conventions

## TypeScript

- Variables, functions, props: `camelCase`.
- Types/interfaces: `PascalCase`.
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` or `camelCase` for config objects.

## Files

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| React components | `kebab-case.tsx` | `login-split-screen.tsx` |
| Server actions / services | `kebab-case.ts` | `sign-in.ts`, `create-user.ts` |
| Config / hooks | `kebab-case.ts` | `navigation.ts`, `use-mobile.ts` |

Export component in `PascalCase`: `LoginSplitScreen` from `login-split-screen.tsx`.

## Prisma / database

- Model fields in schema may use `snake_case` with `@map` / `@@map`.
- In application TypeScript, prefer `camelCase` when reading Prisma client results unless using raw field names.

## Imports

- Use `@/` path alias (`@/features/...`, `@/components/...`, `@/lib/...`).
- `features/*` must not be imported from `lib/*` (dependency flows down: `app` → `features` → `components` → `lib`).
